The main navigation channel of theRhine, blocked by two sunken boats, will remain closed at leastuntil the beginning of next week, a water authority spokesmansaid today.    Karlsruhe water authorities said a queue of about 70 shipshad formed between the towns of Speyer and Iffezheim but mostshipping companies had unloaded cargoes and were usingalternative means of transport.    Heinz-Josef Recker, of the Mannheim water authority, saidtwo floating cranes would make a fresh attempt to raise thesunken tug and its lighter after an unsuccessful try on Friday.The tug Orinoko hit a railway bridge last Tuesday and sank witha cargo of 3,500 tonnes of gravel on board. Before theaccident, about 100 ships a day sailed under the bridge. Reuter&#3;